---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Seedance Prompt Guide - How to Write Perfect AI Video Prompts">
  <div class="guide-page">
    <div class="container">
      <header class="guide-header">
        <h1>Seedance Prompt <span class="gradient-text">Writing Guide</span></h1>
        <p>Master the art of creating cinematic AI videos with perfectly structured prompts</p>
      </header>

      <nav class="toc">
        <h3>üìë Table of Contents</h3>
        <ol>
          <li><a href="#basics">Basic Structure</a></li>
          <li><a href="#camera">Camera Movements</a></li>
          <li><a href="#style">Style & Lighting</a></li>
          <li><a href="#advanced">Advanced Techniques</a></li>
          <li><a href="#tips">Pro Tips</a></li>
        </ol>
      </nav>

      <article class="guide-content">
        <!-- Basic Structure -->
        <section id="basics" class="guide-section">
          <h2>1. Basic Prompt Structure</h2>
          <p>Every effective Seedance prompt follows this formula:</p>
          
          <div class="formula-box">
            <code>Subject + Action + Camera + Scene + Style</code>
          </div>

          <div class="example-grid">
            <div class="example-card">
              <h4>‚ùå Bad Prompt</h4>
              <code>A woman walking in the city</code>
              <p>Too vague. No camera info, no style, no emotion.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="example-card good">
              <h4>‚úÖ Good Prompt</h4>
              <code>A young woman in a red dress walks confidently down a rain-soaked Tokyo street at night. Neon signs reflect in puddles. Camera tracks alongside her with slight handheld movement. Cinematic color grading, moody atmosphere, 35mm film look.</code>
              <p>Specific subject, clear action, camera movement, atmosphere, and style.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </section>

        <!-- Camera Movements -->
        <section id="camera" class="guide-section">
          <h2>2. Camera Movements</h2>
          <p>Seedance excels at understanding camera language. Here are the movements you can use:</p>

          <div class="camera-grid">
            <div class="camera-item">
              <span class="camera-icon">üé¨</span>
              <h4>Push In / Dolly In</h4>
              <p>Camera moves toward subject. Creates intimacy.</p>
              <code>"Camera slowly pushes in from medium shot to close-up"</code>
            </div>
            <div class="camera-item">
              <span class="camera-icon">üîÑ</span>
              <h4>Orbit / Arc</h4>
              <p>Camera circles around subject. Great for reveals.</p>
              <code>"Camera orbits 180 degrees around the product"</code>
            </div>
            <div class="camera-item">
              <span class="camera-icon">üì∑</span>
              <h4>Pan</h4>
              <p>Camera rotates horizontally on axis.</p>
              <code>"Slow pan from left to right across the landscape"</code>
            </div>
            <div class="camera-item">
              <span class="camera-icon">‚¨ÜÔ∏è</span>
              <h4>Tilt</h4>
              <p>Camera rotates vertically. Good for scale.</p>
              <code>"Camera tilts up from feet to face"</code>
            </div>
            <div class="camera-item">
              <span class="camera-icon">üöÅ</span>
              <h4>Aerial / Drone</h4>
              <p>High angle moving shot. Epic views.</p>
              <code>"Aerial drone shot rises over mountain peaks"</code>
            </div>
            <div class="camera-item">
              <span class="camera-icon">üèÉ</span>
              <h4>Tracking / Follow</h4>
              <p>Camera follows subject movement.</p>
              <code>"Camera tracks alongside running athlete"</code>
            </div>
            <div class="camera-item">
              <span class="camera-icon">ü§≥</span>
              <h4>Handheld</h4>
              <p>Slight shake for documentary feel.</p>
              <code>"Handheld camera with subtle movement"</code>
            </div>
            <div class="camera-item">
              <span class="camera-icon">üé•</span>
              <h4>Lens Switch</h4>
              <p>Cut between different shots. Seedance specialty!</p>
              <code>"Wide shot... lens switch to close-up of eyes"</code>
            </div>
          </div>
        </section>

        <!-- Style & Lighting -->
        <section id="style" class="guide-section">
          <h2>3. Style & Lighting</h2>
          
          <h3>Lighting Keywords</h3>
          <div class="keyword-list">
            <span class="keyword">golden hour</span>
            <span class="keyword">blue hour</span>
            <span class="keyword">high-key</span>
            <span class="keyword">low-key</span>
            <span class="keyword">rim lighting</span>
            <span class="keyword">backlit</span>
            <span class="keyword">volumetric</span>
            <span class="keyword">three-point lighting</span>
            <span class="keyword">neon</span>
            <span class="keyword">candlelight</span>
            <span class="keyword">moonlight</span>
            <span class="keyword">studio lighting</span>
          </div>

          <h3>Style References</h3>
          <div class="keyword-list">
            <span class="keyword">cinematic</span>
            <span class="keyword">documentary</span>
            <span class="keyword">commercial</span>
            <span class="keyword">film noir</span>
            <span class="keyword">anime style</span>
            <span class="keyword">Studio Ghibli</span>
            <span class="keyword">Blade Runner aesthetic</span>
            <span class="keyword">Wes Anderson style</span>
            <span class="keyword">35mm film</span>
            <span class="keyword">IMAX</span>
            <span class="keyword">VHS aesthetic</span>
            <span class="keyword">4K HDR</span>
          </div>
        </section>

        <!-- Advanced Techniques -->
        <section id="advanced" class="guide-section">
          <h2>4. Advanced Techniques</h2>

          <h3>Multi-Shot Sequences</h3>
          <p>Use "lens switch" to create cuts within a single generation:</p>
          <div class="code-block">
Wide establishing shot of a futuristic laboratory with scientists working.
<strong>Lens switch</strong> to close-up of a holographic display showing DNA strands rotating.
<strong>Lens switch</strong> to medium shot of lead scientist nodding with satisfaction.
          </div>

          <h3>Image-to-Video (I2V)</h3>
          <p>When using a reference image, focus on describing <em>motion</em> not static elements:</p>
          <div class="example-grid">
            <div class="example-card">
              <h4>‚ùå Bad I2V Prompt</h4>
              <code>A beautiful woman with blue eyes and blonde hair wearing a white dress</code>
              <p>Describes what's already in the image.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="example-card good">
              <h4>‚úÖ Good I2V Prompt</h4>
              <code>She slowly turns her head toward the camera and smiles gently. A light breeze moves her hair. Camera pushes in slightly.</code>
              <p>Focuses on motion and changes.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <h3>Degree Adverbs</h3>
          <p>Seedance responds to intensity modifiers:</p>
          <div class="keyword-list">
            <span class="keyword">slowly</span>
            <span class="keyword">quickly</span>
            <span class="keyword">dramatically</span>
            <span class="keyword">gently</span>
            <span class="keyword">vigorously</span>
            <span class="keyword">frantically</span>
            <span class="keyword">smoothly</span>
            <span class="keyword">abruptly</span>
          </div>
        </section>

        <!-- Pro Tips -->
        <section id="tips" class="guide-section">
          <h2>5. Pro Tips</h2>

          <div class="tips-grid">
            <div class="tip-card">
              <span class="tip-number">01</span>
              <h4>Be Specific with Physics</h4>
              <p>Don't say "car turns." Say "The tires smoke as the car drifts 90 degrees." Seedance calculates physics based on your description.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="tip-card">
              <span class="tip-number">02</span>
              <h4>Use Fixed vs Unfixed Camera</h4>
              <p>Enable "Fixed Camera" in settings for static shots. Disable it when you want camera movement. This overrides prompt instructions.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="tip-card">
              <span class="tip-number">03</span>
              <h4>Test at 5 Seconds First</h4>
              <p>Before generating a 15-second video, test your prompt at 5 seconds to save credits and iterate faster.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="tip-card">
              <span class="tip-number">04</span>
              <h4>Avoid Contradictions</h4>
              <p>If your reference image shows a man, don't write "a woman dancing." Match your prompt to the input.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="tip-card">
              <span class="tip-number">05</span>
              <h4>One Clear Action Per Shot</h4>
              <p>Complex prompts work better when each shot has one primary action. Use lens switches for variety.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="tip-card">
              <span class="tip-number">06</span>
              <h4>Include Sound Cues (2.0)</h4>
              <p>Seedance 2.0 generates audio. Include sound descriptions: "metallic clink," "echoing footsteps," "crackling fire."</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </section>

        <!-- CTA -->
        <div class="guide-cta">
          <h2>Ready to Create?</h2>
          <p>Browse our library of tested prompts and start generating</p>
          <a href="/#prompts" class="btn btn-primary btn-lg">
            Browse Prompts
            <svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2">
              <path d="M7 17L17 7M17 7H7M17 7V17"/>
            </svg>
          </a>
        </div>
      </article>
    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>

<style>
  .guide-page {
    padding: 3rem 0 6rem;
  }

  .guide-header {
    text-align: center;
    margin-bottom: 3rem;
  }

  .guide-header h1 {
    font-size: 3rem;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .guide-header p {
    font-size: 1.25rem;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
  }

  /* TOC */
  .toc {
    background: var(--bg-card);
    border: 1px solid var(--border-color);
    border-radius: var(--radius-lg);
    padding: 1.5rem 2rem;
    margin-bottom: 3rem;
  }

  .toc h3 {
    font-size: 1rem;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    color: var(--text-muted);
  }

  .toc ol {
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    gap: 1rem 2rem;
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    margin: 0;
  }

  .toc a {
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    font-weight: 500;
  }

  .toc a:hover {
    color: var(--accent-primary);
  }

  /* Guide Content */
  .guide-content {
    max-width: 900px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  .guide-section {
    margin-bottom: 4rem;
    padding-bottom: 4rem;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border-color);
  }

  .guide-section:last-of-type {
    border-bottom: none;
  }

  .guide-section h2 {
    font-size: 1.75rem;
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
    color: var(--accent-primary);
  }

  .guide-section h3 {
    font-size: 1.25rem;
    margin: 2rem 0 1rem;
  }

  .guide-section p {
    font-size: 1.05rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
  }

  /* Formula Box */
  .formula-box {
    background: var(--bg-secondary);
    border: 2px solid var(--accent-primary);
    border-radius: var(--radius-lg);
    padding: 1.5rem;
    text-align: center;
    margin: 2rem 0;
  }

  .formula-box code {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 1.25rem;
    color: var(--accent-primary);
  }

  /* Example Grid */
  .example-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);
    gap: 1.5rem;
    margin: 2rem 0;
  }

  .example-card {
    background: var(--bg-card);
    border: 1px solid var(--border-color);
    border-radius: var(--radius-lg);
    padding: 1.5rem;
  }

  .example-card.good {
    border-color: var(--accent-primary);
  }

  .example-card h4 {
    font-size: 1rem;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .example-card code {
    display: block;
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    background: var(--bg-primary);
    padding: 1rem;
    border-radius: var(--radius-md);
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    line-height: 1.6;
  }

  .example-card p {
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    margin: 0;
  }

  /* Camera Grid */
  .camera-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);
    gap: 1rem;
    margin: 2rem 0;
  }

  .camera-item {
    background: var(--bg-card);
    border: 1px solid var(--border-color);
    border-radius: var(--radius-lg);
    padding: 1.25rem;
  }

  .camera-icon {
    font-size: 1.5rem;
    display: block;
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  .camera-item h4 {
    font-size: 1rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  .camera-item p {
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
    color: var(--text-muted);
  }

  .camera-item code {
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    color: var(--accent-primary);
  }

  /* Keywords */
  .keyword-list {
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    gap: 0.5rem;
    margin: 1rem 0 2rem;
  }

  .keyword {
    padding: 0.4rem 0.75rem;
    background: var(--bg-tertiary);
    border: 1px solid var(--border-color);
    border-radius: var(--radius-sm);
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
  }

  /* Code Block */
  .code-block {
    background: var(--bg-primary);
    border: 1px solid var(--border-color);
    border-radius: var(--radius-lg);
    padding: 1.5rem;
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    line-height: 1.8;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    white-space: pre-wrap;
    margin: 1rem 0 2rem;
  }

  .code-block strong {
    color: var(--accent-primary);
  }

  /* Tips Grid */
  .tips-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);
    gap: 1.5rem;
  }

  .tip-card {
    background: var(--bg-card);
    border: 1px solid var(--border-color);
    border-radius: var(--radius-lg);
    padding: 1.5rem;
    position: relative;
  }

  .tip-number {
    position: absolute;
    top: 1rem;
    right: 1rem;
    font-size: 2rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--bg-tertiary);
  }

  .tip-card h4 {
    font-size: 1rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
    color: var(--accent-primary);
  }

  .tip-card p {
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    margin: 0;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
  }

  /* CTA */
  .guide-cta {
    text-align: center;
    padding: 3rem;
    background: var(--bg-secondary);
    border: 1px solid var(--border-color);
    border-radius: var(--radius-xl);
    margin-top: 4rem;
  }

  .guide-cta h2 {
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  .guide-cta p {
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
    color: var(--text-muted);
  }

  .btn-lg {
    padding: 1rem 2rem;
    font-size: 1rem;
  }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .guide-header h1 {
      font-size: 2rem;
    }

    .example-grid,
    .camera-grid,
    .tips-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }

    .toc ol {
      flex-direction: column;
      gap: 0.75rem;
    }
  }
</style>
